The paper deals with a data structure for dynamic nearest neighbor queries in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the update and query time complexities of the data structure, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions applications of the data structure in constructing spanners and connectivity queries, which are related to cs.GR (Graph Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the sites used in the distance functions, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
